(n - 1)2^{n+1} + 2 + (n+1)2^{n+1} = n(2^{n+2})+2
\begin{align}\color{darkred}{\bf(n - 1)}\color{blue}{\bf 2^{n+1}} + 2 + \color{darkred}{\bf (n+1)}\color{blue}{\bf 2^{n+1}} & = \color{darkred}{\bf(n - 1 + n+1)}\color{blue}{\bf 2^{n+1}} + 2 \\ \\ & = 2n\cdot2^{n+1} +2 \\ \\  & = n\cdot 2\cdot 2^{n+1} + 2 \\ \\ & = n\cdot 2^{n+2} + 2 \\ \\ \end{align}
a\cdot 2^{n+1} + b\cdot 2^{n+1} = (a+b)\cdot 2^{n+1}
a=n-1
b=n+1
a+b=2n
A=2^n
2^{n+1}=2\cdot 2^n=2A
2^{n+2}=2^2\cdot 2^n = 4A
2(n - 1)A + 2 + 2(n+1)A = 4nA+2.
2(n - 1)A + 2 + 2(n+1)A = 2A(n-1+n+1)+2=2A(2n)+2=4nA+2,
